---
import { debtServiceData, mobileData } from "../../data/charts";
import BarChart from "../charts/BarChart.astro";
import SankeyChart from "../charts/SankeyChart.astro";
import StatNumber from "../StatNumber.astro";
---

<section id="imperialism" aria-labelledby="imperialism-heading">
	<div class="two-col imperialism-layout">
		<div class="col-charts">
			<div class="stat-grid reveal">
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-imp-0">
					<StatNumber target={2} prefix="$" suffix="T" />
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-imp-0">
						Net annual resource flows from South to North — Hickel et al. 2021<button type="button" class="cite-ref" aria-label="View source: Hickel et al. 2021" aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false" data-source="Hickel, Sullivan &amp; Zoomkawala, New Political Economy, 2021" data-url="https://doi.org/10.1080/13563467.2021.1899153">*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-imp-1">
					<StatNumber target={21} suffix="%" />
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-imp-1">
						Of South Africa's government revenue goes to debt service in
						2023/24 — nearly double the 12% share in 2015, driven by
						state capture and its aftermath<button type="button" class="cite-ref" aria-label="View source: National Treasury South Africa" aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false" data-source="National Treasury South Africa, Budget Review 2024" data-url="https://www.treasury.gov.za/documents/national%20budget/2024/review/FullBR.pdf">*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-imp-2">
					<StatNumber target={54} />
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-imp-2">Countries in debt crisis or at high risk — UN 2025</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-imp-3">
					<StatNumber target={443} prefix="$" suffix="B" />
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-imp-3">
						Annual debt service payments by developing countries — 2022 (World Bank)<button type="button" class="cite-ref" aria-label="View source: World Bank 2023" aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false" data-source="World Bank, International Debt Report, 2023" data-url="https://www.worldbank.org/en/publication/international-debt-report">*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<figure class="chart-box reveal">
				<figcaption class="chart-title">The Real Flow of Wealth: South to North</figcaption>
				<div id="flows-sankey-desktop-chart" class="desktop-chart" role="img" aria-label="Sankey diagram showing the real flow of wealth from South to North: $10.8 trillion in unequal exchange versus only $200 billion in aid. South Africa sits on both sides of this flow — as a victim of colonial extraction and as a source of ongoing capital flight.">
					<SankeyChart />
				</div>
				<div id="flows-sankey-mobile-chart" class="mobile-chart" role="img" aria-label="Bar chart showing wealth flows from Global South to North">
					<BarChart id="sankey-mobile-bars" items={mobileData.sankey} outsideValueThreshold={15} />
				</div>
				<table class="sr-only">
					<caption>The Real Flow of Wealth: South to North</caption>
					<thead><tr><th>Flow</th><th>Direction</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td>Unequal Exchange</td><td>South to North</td><td>$10.8T</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Debt Service</td><td>South to North</td><td>$443B</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Illicit Flows</td><td>South to North</td><td>$89B</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Aid</td><td>North to South</td><td>$200B</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</figure>
			<figure class="chart-box reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.12s">
				<figcaption class="chart-title">Debt Service as % of Government Revenue</figcaption>
				<div role="img" aria-label="Bar chart showing debt service as percentage of government revenue: Sri Lanka 73%, Ghana 47%, Pakistan 40%, Kenya 30%, South Africa approximately 21%, USA 9%, UK 7%">
					<BarChart id="debt-service-chart" items={debtServiceData} outsideValueThreshold={13} />
				</div>
			</figure>
		</div>
		<div class="col-text">
			<div class="section-label reveal-left">Global South &amp; Colonialism</div>
			<h2 id="imperialism-heading" class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.1s">
				Extraction<br />Without Borders
			</h2>
			<p>
				South Africa's extraction story did not begin in 1948. It began in
				1652, accelerated with diamonds in 1867 and gold in 1886, and was
				systematised by a British colonial state that dispossessed, taxed,
				and conscripted an entire people into its mines. The apartheid
				state inherited this structure and perfected it. And when majority
				rule came, South African mining capital — Anglo American, Glencore,
				Gold Fields — did not dissolve. It registered in Bermuda, listed
				in London, and continued extracting value from the same soil, the
				same workers, the same communities.
			</p>
			<p>
				When illicit financial flows, debt service, trade mispricing, and
				unequal exchange are accounted for, the Global South is a net
				creditor to the Global North — transferring an estimated $2
				trillion per year northward. South Africa is not only a victim
				of this system — through its own mining capital, it runs the
				same operation within Africa. The same logic that London
				applied to Johannesburg, Johannesburg applies to the
				rest of the continent.
			</p>
			<p>
				South Africa's debt cost has nearly doubled since the state
				capture years (2009–2018), during which Zuma-aligned networks
				looted an estimated R500 billion from state enterprises. The
				interest bill on that looting now crowds out healthcare, housing,
				and education budgets — transferring the cost of elite theft onto
				the public permanently.
			</p>
			<div class="pull-quote reveal">
				<blockquote>"Europe is literally the creation of the Third World."</blockquote>
				<cite>— Frantz Fanon, <em>The Wretched of the Earth</em>, 1961</cite>
			</div>
			<p class="source">
				Source: Jason Hickel, <em>The Divide</em> ·
				<a href="https://gfintegrity.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Global Financial Integrity</a> ·
				<a href="https://www.treasury.gov.za" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">National Treasury SA</a> ·
				<a href="https://data.worldbank.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">World Bank</a> ·
				<a href="https://unctad.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">UNCTAD</a>
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
